}
</script>

<div class="bm-product mockingbird-product">
  <nav class="bm-topbar bm-wrap" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
    <a href="/collections/universal-in-ear">Universal In-Ear</a>
    <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
    <span aria-current="page">Mockingbird</span>
  </nav>

  <aside class="bm-floating-buy" aria-label="Mockingbird price and purchase">
    <span class="bm-floating-buy__label">Mockingbird</span>
    <strong>{{ product_price }}</strong>
    {% if current_variant.available %}
      <a href="/cart/add?id={{ current_variant.id }}&quantity=1">Buy</a>
    {% else %}
      <span>Sold out</span>
    {% endif %}
  </aside>

  <section class="bm-hero bm-wrap" aria-labelledby="mockingbird-title">
    <div class="bm-hero__copy">
      <p class="bm-kicker">Nine-driver hybrid reference in-ear monitor</p>
      <h1 id="mockingbird-title">Mockingbird</h1>
      <p class="bm-hero__lead">Successor to the acclaimed W900. Nine drivers across four dedicated frequency bands. Proprietary tuned dynamic woofer for natural sub-bass. Bespoke super tweeter armatures extend to 40kHz. TrueXross 4-way crossover eliminates phase shift for high-end speaker-like coherence. Universal or custom fit.</p>
      <p class="bm-price"><span>Price</span><strong>{{ product_price }}</strong></p>
      <div class="bm-judge-stars" aria-label="Mockingbird customer rating">
        <div class="jdgm-widget jdgm-preview-badge" data-id="{{ product.id }}" data-auto-install="false">
          {{ jm_badge }}
        </div>
        {% if jm_badge == blank or jm_badge contains 'No reviews' %}
          <span class="bm-rating-fallback" aria-label="Customer review archive">
            <span aria-hidden="true">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</span>
            <span>Review archive</span>
          </span>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      <ul class="bm-pill-list" aria-label="Mockingbird highlights">
        <li>9-driver hybrid</li>
        <li>TrueXross crossover</li>
        <li>Bespoke super tweeter</li>
        <li>Universal/custom</li>
      </ul>
      <form class="bm-actions" method="post" action="/cart/add" enctype="multipart/form-data">
        <input type="hidden" name="id" value="{{ current_variant.id }}">
        <input type="hidden" name="quantity" value="1">
        <button class="bm-btn" type="submit"{% unless current_variant.available %} disabled{% endunless %}>{% if current_variant.available %}Buy Mockingbird{% else %}Sold Out{% endif %}</button>
        <a class="bm-btn bm-btn--ghost" href="#mockingbird-architecture">Explore the build</a>
      </form>
    </div>
    <figure class="bm-hero__media">
      <img src="{{ 'mockingbird-hero.png' | asset_url }}" alt="AAW Mockingbird nine-driver hybrid reference universal in-ear monitors with detachable cable" width="2000" height="1334" loading="eager">
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="bm-stat-band" aria-label="Mockingbird specification highlights">
    <div class="bm-wrap bm-stats">
      <article><b>9</b><span>Hybrid drivers. Universal or custom fit.</span></article>
      <article><b>4-way</b><span>TrueXross crossover network.</span></article>
      <article><b>10Hz-40kHz</b><span>Frequency response with bespoke super tweeters.</span></article>
      <article><b>15 Ohm</b><span>Impedance. Drives from any source.</span></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bm-section bm-story">
    <div class="bm-wrap bm-story__grid">
      <div>
        <p class="bm-kicker">Design Story</p>
        <h2>Successor to the W900. Reference, redefined.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="bm-prose">
        <p>Mockingbird is the successor to AAW's acclaimed W900 and represents the summit of our ideology: fusing the best traits of dynamic and balanced armature drivers into a single coherent stage. Instead of using high-order RC crossover networks that introduce chaotic phase shift and scrambled arrival timing, AAW developed TrueXross — a completely new approach to solving the classic coherence issue in hybrid earphones.</p>
        <p>The dynamic driver is proprietary tuned at the diaphragm level. A physical low-pass filter further restricts it to a minimal overlapping frequency range relative to the balanced armature drivers. Combined with precise positional arrangement and front acoustic chamber design, the result is improved coherence, minimized phase shift, and optimized arrival timing across the entire spectrum.</p>
        <p>Built as true reference equipment: powerful yet natural sub-bass you will never find in a full balanced armature IEM, inherited AAW musical imaging and instrument separation, and a realistic sound stage stepped up with extended treble and superior detail retrieval. Same driver platform, same TrueXross crossover — universal or custom.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bm-section bm-section--dark">
    <div class="bm-wrap bm-section-head">
      <p class="bm-kicker">Fitment Options</p>
      <h2>Available in universal and custom fit.</h2>
      <p>Universal fit ships with LiquidMorph tips, AAW foam tips, and assorted silicone tips. Custom fit is built from ear impressions. Both use the same nine-driver hybrid reference platform.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bm-wrap mockingbird-original-grid">
      <figure>
        <img src="{{ 'mockingbird-universal.png' | asset_url }}" alt="AAW Mockingbird universal in-ear monitors with detachable cable" width="2000" height="1334" loading="lazy">
        <figcaption><b>Universal fit</b><span>Ships with LiquidMorph and foam tips. Stable seal, quick sizing, daily handling.</span></figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure>
        <img src="{{ 'aaw-ins-hero-ciem-2026.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="AAW custom-fit in-ear monitors showing personalized shell and faceplate finish" width="1200" height="900" loading="lazy">
        <figcaption><b>Custom fit</b><span>Built from ear impressions. Personalized shell, stronger isolation.</span></figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bm-section bm-section--dark" id="mockingbird-architecture">
    <div class="bm-wrap bm-section-head">
      <p class="bm-kicker">Acoustic Architecture</p>
      <h2>TrueXross crossover. No chaotic phase shift. One coherent stage.</h2>
      <p>Traditional high-order RC crossover networks create phase shift and scrambled arrival timing in hybrid earphones. TrueXross eliminates this — the dynamic driver uses a physical low-pass filter so it operates in a minimal overlapping range versus the armatures. Precise positional arrangement and front acoustic chamber design then align the wavefronts. Mockingbird uses a 4-way crossover network with dedicated woofer, mid, treble, and super tweeter paths. The bespoke super tweeter armatures — developed with the world's leading BA manufacturer — sustain sound pressure to 20kHz and extend to 40kHz.</p>
