      <p class="bm-kicker">Sound Signature &amp; Frequency Response</p>
      <h2>Reference performance. Measured and verified.</h2>
      <p>Mockingbird is tuned as true reference equipment. The frequency response is the result of TrueXross 4-way crossover tuning — proprietary dynamic woofer delivers natural sub-bass extension, and the bespoke super tweeters sustain output past 20kHz. Every driver band is shaped for phase coherence, not just amplitude. The end result is high-end speaker-like performance condensed into the tiny footprint of an IEM.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bm-wrap mockingbird-switch-grid" aria-label="Mockingbird sound characteristics">
      <article><span>Low</span><h3>Natural sub-bass</h3><p>Proprietary tuned dynamic woofer delivers powerful yet natural low-end you will never find in a full BA IEM. Physical low-pass filter keeps it clean and phase-coherent.</p></article>
      <article><span>Mid</span><h3>Acclaimed imaging</h3><p>Inherits AAW's highly praised musical imaging and instrument separation. Vocals and instruments sit in a realistic, layered sound stage with precise positioning.</p></article>
      <article><span>High</span><h3>Extended treble</h3><p>Bespoke super tweeters sustain SPL to 20kHz and extend to 40kHz. Superior detail retrieval without fatigue. Cymbal air, string harmonics, room cues — all present and natural.</p></article>
      <article><span>Stage</span><h3>Speaker-like coherence</h3><p>TrueXross eliminates phase shift and scrambled timing. Wide stage, accurate positioning, layered depth. Nine drivers performing as one coherent source.</p></article>
    </div>
    <div class="bm-wrap" style="margin-top:34px">
      <figure style="margin:0;background:#0a0a0a;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);overflow:hidden">
        <img src="{{ 'mockingbird-frequency-response-graph.png' | asset_url }}" alt="AAW Mockingbird frequency response measurement graph showing TrueXross 4-way crossover tuning with extended treble to 40kHz" width="2000" height="1100" loading="lazy" style="display:block;width:100%;height:auto">
        <figcaption style="padding:18px 24px;color:#d4cec7;font-size:14px;line-height:1.5">TrueXross 4-way frequency response. The proprietary dynamic woofer handles the low end with a physical low-pass filter to minimize overlap. The bespoke super tweeters extend treble to 40kHz. Every band is shaped for phase coherence at the crossover points.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

