  <section class="bm-section bm-section--dark bm-faq">
    <div class="bm-wrap bm-section-head">
      <p class="bm-kicker">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Before you choose Mockingbird</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="bm-wrap" style="max-width:820px;margin:0 auto">
      <div class="bm-faq__list">
        <details>
          <summary><span>What is the Mockingbird driver configuration?</span></summary>
          <p>Nine-driver hybrid reference monitor. One proprietary tuned dynamic woofer with physical low-pass filter for natural sub-bass. Eight balanced armature drivers including bespoke super tweeters covering mids, treble, and ultra-high frequencies. TrueXross 4-way crossover network.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What is TrueXross?</span></summary>
          <p>TrueXross is AAW's proprietary approach to solving the classic coherence issue in hybrid earphones. Instead of using high-order RC crossover networks that cause chaotic phase shift and scrambled arrival timing, TrueXross uses a physical low-pass filter on the dynamic driver so it operates in a minimal overlapping frequency range relative to the balanced armature drivers. Combined with precise positional arrangement and front acoustic chamber design, this achieves improved coherence, minimized phase shift, and optimized arrival timing.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What are the bespoke super tweeter drivers?</span></summary>
          <p>AAW worked with the world's leading balanced armature manufacturer to develop custom super tweeter drivers exclusively for Mockingbird. These bespoke drivers sustain sound pressure level all the way to 20kHz and extend to 40kHz, delivering extended treble and superior detail retrieval that gives Mockingbird its high-end speaker-like performance.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Is Mockingbird available as universal and custom fit?</span></summary>
          <p>Yes. Universal-fit units ship with LiquidMorph tips, AAW foam tips, and assorted silicone tips. Custom-fit units are built from ear impressions. Both use the same nine-driver hybrid reference platform.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What sound signature does Mockingbird have?</span></summary>
          <p>True reference signature. Powerful yet natural sub-bass that full BA IEMs cannot reproduce. Inherits AAW's highly praised musical imaging, instrument separation, and realistic sound stage. The bespoke super tweeters deliver extended treble and superior detail retrieval. The end result is high-end speaker-like performance in an IEM footprint.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>What comes in the box?</span></summary>
          <p>48 inch Null Audio Symphonym Tiburon UPOCC copper detachable cable, wooden AAW carry case, LiquidMorph tips, AAW short-stem foam tips (S/M/L), AAW assorted silicone tips (S/M/L x2). One-year limited warranty.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

